headline: JP Morgan upgrades Yum Brands on growth under new CEO
summary: Investing.com -- JP Morgan upgraded Yum Brands to Overweight from Neutral, citing consistent unit growth, strong free cash flow, and a more attractive valuation following a pullback in the stock.“Newly appointed CEO Chris Turner is likely to continue tech focus to drive franchisee returns,” analysts at JP Morgan wrote.
